revision.text:
{{unreferenced|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox football league season | competition = 2016 K3 League | logo = | season = 2016 | winners = | continentalcup1 = | continentalcup1 qualifiers = | league topscorer = | matches = | total goals = | highest attendance = | lowest attendance = | average attendance = | prevseason = [[2015 K3 League|2015]] | nextseason = [[2017 K3 League Advanced|2017(A)]] [[2017 K3 League Basic|2017(B)]] }} <!--{{Challengers League map 2016}}--> The '''2016 K3 League''' was the tenth season of the [[K3 League]]. After 2015 season Seoul FC Martyrs left the league, but three new teams Buyeo FC, Siheung Citizen, and Yangpyeong FC joined it.
== Competition format == The 2016 season runs from March through to October. The 20 teams compete in a single division. Each team plays each other once for a total of 19 games. After the regular season, the top 11 teams will qualify for the 2017 K3 League Advanced. The playoff winner of 4 teams ranked 12th to 15th will also qualify for 2017 K3 League Advanced. The remaining 8 teams will compete in the 2017 K3 League Basic.
