{{infobox country at games | NOC = LBR | NOCname = Liberia National Olympic Committee | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1988 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Seoul]] | competitors = 8 | sports = 2 | flagbearer = [[Samuel Birch (athlete)|Samuel Birch]] | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Liberia]]''' competed at the '''[[1988 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea|Korea]]. They had a very poor showing, despite their magnificent send-off. Two members of the official delegation were assaulted upon their return because of the perceived embarrassment suffered by the nation at their expense.
